Provides: grub-efi-amd64, grub-efi-amd64-bin, grub-common, grub2-common
Description: GRUB2 EFI binary and userspace for amd64 (BLS, Secure Boot)
 Provides a GRUB2 EFI binary (grubx64.efi) plus the full grub2-* userspace
 (grub2-editenv, grub2-install, grub2-mkconfig, x86_64-efi modules, fonts),
 compiled from the Fedora rhboot/grub2 fork with BLS (Boot Loader
 Specification) support required by ostree and bootc, and signed with the
 debian-bootc Secure Boot signing key. It fully supersedes Debian's
 grub-common/grub2-common so the naming matches bootupd's grub2-* tooling.
 .
 The binary is verified by the shim bootloader through the MOK (Machine
 Owner Key) mechanism. The signing certificate is included at
 /usr/share/debian-bootc/sb_signing.crt and automatically queued for MOK
 enrollment via the package postinst script. Enrollment confirmation is
 required at the MokManager screen on the next reboot.
